body:
Hey, same issue here. At first I thought I had done something wrong, but now I realize that others have faced the same issue too. Calling different animations using the same lottieAnimationView leads to some calls being skipped entirely.

**Use case**

I'm using  lottieAnimationView as a button that requires the animation to played each time the user interacts with it. 

**Example Code**
```
LottieAnimationView animView = (LottieAnimationView) findViewById(R.id.lottieview);

 animView.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {  
            @Override  
            public void onClick(View view)
           {  
               if(condition)
                       animView .setAnimation("lottie1.json");                  // lottie1 and lottie2 files in assets folder
               else
                       animView .setAnimation("lottie2.json");
                
               animView.playAnimation();

            }  
});  
```
**Issue**

 The first 2-3 button clicks _usually_ runs as expected with animView easily transitioning between lottie1 and lottie2 animation (looping=false) during a button press and then back to lottie1. However after that , even though the button click event occurs successfully, the lottieview fails to render and remains blank ðŸ˜¶ðŸ˜¶. This occurs randomly, though I've noticed that it usually starts during the 5th or 6th transition.

**Lottie Build Version :** 3.6.0
**Android Version :** Android 10
